HEADWORD: Earcockle
<hw>Ear"coc`kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A disease in wheat, in which the blackened and contracted grain, or
ear, is filled with minute worms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

